[0m$ [0mgit add -A && git commit -m "fix(agents): simplify isEnvVarLine to use strict regex

BUG-03: isEnvVarLine had wrong operator precedence with
strings.Contains(line, \"=\") && !strings.Contains(line, \" \") ||
regexp.MustCompile(...).MatchString(line)

The first clause could misclassify cron command arguments containing
'=' (e.g. make test=1) if there's no space after the '='.

Fix: Use only the regex ^[A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*=[^ ]*$ which:
- Matches lines starting with KEY=
- Only allows non-space characters after '=' (handles PATH with colons)
- Rejects lines with command content after the env var (space terminates)

Tests: go test -race ./... passes"
